Coconut Roti - Sri Lankan Coconut Rice Flatbread
  --Girl Cooks World

2 c rice flour
1/2 c unsweetened, dried and shredded coconut
1/2 tsp salt
~1 - 1 1/2 c water

Plase flour in a large skillet over medium heat. Stir the flour continuously to ensure even toasting. Remove from heat when the flour has darkened several shades and emits a toasted aroma. Place in a large bowl. In the same skillet, toast the coconut, stirring constantly, just until it brgins to turn golden. Add coconut to the bowl with the flour and add salt; stir to combine. Add just enough water to make a soft dough. Knead until it forms a ball and no longer sticks to the side of the bowl. To test the moisture level, roll a bit of the dough in your hand and press it flat. It should easily stay in one piece but it should also have some cracking around the edges. If the edges are smooth, you've added too much water. In this case, you can add some untoasted rice flour to the mixture. Roll the dough into balls about the size of a golf ball. Place each ball between 2 pieces of waxed paper and use your palm or rolling pin to flatten to your desired thickness. If you're a rotie n00b, probably want to keep them on the thicker side; if you make them too thin, they can break easily. Fry on a preheated, lightly greased griddle or frypan over medium to medium high heat until it begins to brown, ~4-5 min. Flip and cook on the other side until golden brown. 

